Summary table for marZIP - Laksh

Source: R/marZIBP_Laksh.R
summary.marZIBP_Laksh.Rd

This function obtains the summary table for objects of class marZIBP_Laksh.

# S3 method for class 'marZIBP_Laksh'
summary(object)

Arguments

object

of class marZIBP_Laksh.

Value

Returns the summary table.

Author

Freddy Hernandez-Barajas, fhernanb@unal.edu.co

# Example 2 ---------------------------------------------------------------

gen_data_ZIBP_Laksh <- function(n=10) {
  # To generate the covariates
  x1 <- runif(n=n)
  x2 <- runif(n=n)

  # To generate the means
  mu1 <- exp(-2 + 3.5 * x1 + 2.7 * x2)
  mu2 <- exp(-1 + 1.3 * x1 + 2.1 * x2)

  # To generate the p
  logit_inv <- function(x) exp(x) / (1+exp(x))
  psi  <- logit_inv(-2.4 + 1.2 * x2)

  alpha <- -1

  # To obtain lambdas
  l1 <- mu1 / (1-psi)
  l2 <- mu2 / (1-psi)

  # To generate Y1 and Y2
  y <- NULL
  for (i in 1:n)
    y <- rbind(y, rZIBP_Laksh(n=1, l1=l1[i], l2=l2[i],
                              alpha=alpha, psi=psi[i]))

  # To create the dataset
  dataset <- data.frame(y1=y[,1], y2=y[,2],
                        x1=x1, x2=x2,
                        mu1=mu1, mu2=mu2,
                        alpha=alpha, psi=psi,
                        l1=l1, l2=l2)

  return(dataset)
}
